WEBVTT

00:00:07.812 --> 00:00:09.022
N-No…

00:00:09.772 --> 00:00:10.774
That's impossible…

00:00:11.149 --> 00:00:13.609
I can't believe the Tres Bestia
were defeated…

00:00:14.361 --> 00:00:17.321
A Soul Reaper with an Arrancar
on his back?

00:00:17.739 --> 00:00:18.948
How unusual.

00:00:19.575 --> 00:00:20.576
That being said…

00:00:20.993 --> 00:00:23.161
I know all about you,

00:00:23.996 --> 00:00:25.956
Ichigo Kurosaki.

00:00:26.832 --> 00:00:31.753
The Daten that His Majesty gave us
included information about you.

00:00:32.170 --> 00:00:34.298
You were listed
as a "Special Threat"

00:00:34.338 --> 00:00:36.341
that we should prioritize
dealing with!

00:00:38.051 --> 00:00:39.219
"Special Threat"?

00:00:41.262 --> 00:00:42.222
<i>That technique…</i>

00:00:43.390 --> 00:00:44.348
<i>the Hirenkyaku.</i>

00:00:53.733 --> 00:00:54.817
Are you guys really Qui--?

00:00:54.942 --> 00:00:55.903
Oh, my!

00:00:55.986 --> 00:01:00.948
Don't tell me that you engaged us
<i>without</i> knowing who we were?

00:01:01.658 --> 00:01:02.659
Very well!

00:01:02.867 --> 00:01:04.828
In that case…
I shall answer your question.

00:01:13.003 --> 00:01:15.756
Yes, we <i>are</i> who you think we are.

00:01:16.381 --> 00:01:17.840
We are <i>Quincies</i>.

00:01:20.718 --> 00:01:24.765
{\an8}SQUAD ONE BARRACKS -
CAPTAIN'S MEETING ROOM

00:01:23.221 --> 00:01:24.472
Quincies…

00:01:25.224 --> 00:01:26.641
Well, I figured
that would be the case,

00:01:26.766 --> 00:01:28.560
but this is quite the problem.

00:01:28.644 --> 00:01:31.021
Where is their base of operations?

00:01:32.355 --> 00:01:34.983
Unfortunately,
I have yet to find it…

00:01:35.233 --> 00:01:36.442
I see…

00:01:36.902 --> 00:01:39.780
That means we have no way
of attacking them.

00:01:41.322 --> 00:01:45.911
I'm ordering all Squad Captains
to prepare for war.

00:01:46.245 --> 00:01:48.037
The advance guard of the rebel army

00:01:48.162 --> 00:01:50.415
announced that the battle
would begin in five days,

00:01:50.748 --> 00:01:53.126
but there is no reason to believe
the words of treacherous fellows

00:01:53.251 --> 00:01:55.378
that would launch
a surprise attack.

00:01:55.795 --> 00:01:58.799
We must prepare for battle at once,
as fast as we possibly can!

00:01:59.424 --> 00:02:02.844
We must not let them
get the upper hand again!

00:02:23.407 --> 00:02:28.245
{\an8}<i>The blue skies above are hopelessly clear</i>

00:02:28.370 --> 00:02:33.417
{\an8}<i>At my wit's end, I feel a growing frustration</i>

00:02:33.834 --> 00:02:38.296
{\an8}<i>As if to laugh at us hopeless cowards</i>

00:02:38.629 --> 00:02:41.758
{\an8}<i>Countless eyes stare at us</i>

00:02:42.508 --> 00:02:48.348
{\an8}<i>This soul of mine breaks again and again</i>

00:02:48.639 --> 00:02:51.560
{\an8}<i>All I can do is hold it tight</i>

00:02:52.769 --> 00:02:57.858
{\an8}<i>Until the day it turns to ash</i>

00:02:57.858 --> 00:03:00.693
{\an8}<i>I've absorbed all of this sorrow</i>

00:03:00.818 --> 00:03:05.324
{\an8}<i>It has shaped me, painted me</i>

00:03:05.407 --> 00:03:07.909
{\an8}<i>But that's how we got here, right?</i>

00:03:08.034 --> 00:03:12.830
{\an8}<i>One step at a time, just like breathing</i>

00:03:12.997 --> 00:03:15.667
{\an8}<i>These countless scars on my palm</i>

00:03:15.792 --> 00:03:17.669
{\an8}<i>That no longer fade</i>

00:03:17.752 --> 00:03:21.423
{\an8}<i>Are my badge, my story</i>

00:03:21.673 --> 00:03:25.343
{\an8}<i>I faced the fear and shred it to pieces</i>

00:03:25.509 --> 00:03:28.513
{\an8}<i>And let it walk beside me once more</i>

00:03:28.597 --> 00:03:33.227
{\an8}BLEACH: THOUSAND-YEAR BLOOD WAR

00:03:55.957 --> 00:03:57.626
All shots hit their mark.

00:03:58.293 --> 00:03:59.502
What's the matter?!

00:03:59.627 --> 00:04:01.587
You can do better than this!

00:04:06.677 --> 00:04:07.636
That's weird…

00:04:09.428 --> 00:04:12.391
I heard that Quincies
only use bows.

00:04:13.432 --> 00:04:14.350
What?

00:04:21.233 --> 00:04:22.358
Kurosaki!

00:04:23.276 --> 00:04:24.278
Inoue!

00:04:24.653 --> 00:04:25.778
Look after Nel!

00:04:32.911 --> 00:04:34.161
Impressive…

00:04:34.829 --> 00:04:38.666
It makes me dismayed
by my lack of skill…

00:04:39.293 --> 00:04:40.418
Don't worry.

00:04:40.711 --> 00:04:43.129
Your arrows were a lot stronger
than Ishida's.

00:04:43.797 --> 00:04:46.007
Though it's been quite some time
since I got hit with one of them.

00:04:46.507 --> 00:04:47.466
"Ishida"?

00:04:48.259 --> 00:04:51.762
By "Ishida,"
are you referring to "Uryu Ishida"?

00:04:52.930 --> 00:04:55.600
You guys know about Ishida?

00:04:56.392 --> 00:05:00.355
Uryu Ishida's Heilig Pfeil
is weaker than mine?

00:05:01.523 --> 00:05:02.940
How odd…

00:05:03.483 --> 00:05:05.319
That's not possible.

00:05:06.028 --> 00:05:07.278
What do you mean?

00:05:07.737 --> 00:05:08.738
Whoops.

00:05:09.113 --> 00:05:11.615
Speech is silver,
silence is golden.

00:05:12.117 --> 00:05:13.910
I've said a little too much.

00:05:14.702 --> 00:05:15.579
Forgive me…

00:05:18.999 --> 00:05:21.752
Now then, it's time for me
to stop fooling around.

00:05:22.209 --> 00:05:24.920
I just received orders
from His Majesty.

00:05:25.422 --> 00:05:26.673
Just who is this "Majesty"?

00:05:27.214 --> 00:05:29.800
I have no need
to answer that question.

00:05:30.634 --> 00:05:33.680
In short, it means
you are going to die here.

00:05:34.598 --> 00:05:36.182
Now take a good look.

00:05:36.557 --> 00:05:40.771
I'm sure you've heard
about this power…

00:05:41.605 --> 00:05:44.815
A Quincy's final state, Letz Stile!

00:05:50.404 --> 00:05:53.449
<i>The Quincy secret move</i>
<i>that Ishida used before!</i>

00:06:03.752 --> 00:06:06.254
Allow me to explain…

00:06:06.588 --> 00:06:08.673
The proper name for this form is…

00:06:09.548 --> 00:06:12.302
Quincy Voll Stern Dich.

00:06:15.596 --> 00:06:17.641
We've received an update
from Jagd Armee 1.

00:06:17.848 --> 00:06:20.976
Quilge Opie is currently
engaged in battle

00:06:21.060 --> 00:06:22.687
with "Special Threat"
Ichigo Kurosaki.

00:06:23.730 --> 00:06:25.899
Then let's go…

00:06:25.982 --> 00:06:28.067
Where to, Your Majesty?

00:06:28.985 --> 00:06:30.821
Isn't it obvious?

00:06:31.446 --> 00:06:33.781
<i>An imperial order from His Majesty</i>
<i>to the Stern Ritter.</i>

00:06:34.240 --> 00:06:37.285
<i>All Stern Ritter are to</i>
<i>immediately get equipped</i>

00:06:37.411 --> 00:06:39.079
<i>and assemble at</i>
<i>the Gate of the Sun.</i>

00:06:39.579 --> 00:06:40.579
<i>Repeat…</i>

00:06:40.788 --> 00:06:41.665
<i>All Stern Ritter are to…</i>

00:06:42.165 --> 00:06:44.584
The Wandenreich is going to…

00:06:45.252 --> 00:06:48.295
invade the Soul Society.

00:07:09.483 --> 00:07:10.776
Do you feel it?

00:07:11.278 --> 00:07:13.947
The pulsation of my power…

00:07:16.115 --> 00:07:19.119
The power of the one
who shall punish you!

00:07:23.540 --> 00:07:26.918
<i>Is that the same technique</i>
<i>that Urahara told me about?</i>

00:07:32.757 --> 00:07:34.718
You seem confused.

00:07:35.050 --> 00:07:36.802
I know what you're thinking,

00:07:36.887 --> 00:07:39.139
so I shall give you
a definitive answer.

00:07:39.639 --> 00:07:41.098
It's something entirely different.

00:07:43.142 --> 00:07:47.646
The Quincy Letz Stile that you know
is a relic of the past

00:07:47.771 --> 00:07:52.694
that died out 200 years ago
due to its fragile nature.

00:07:52.819 --> 00:07:56.656
The only one who was attached to it
was Soken Ishida,

00:07:56.697 --> 00:07:59.533
who rejected our research
and evolution!

00:07:59.701 --> 00:08:02.704
By comparison,
this Quincy Voll Stern Dich…

00:08:04.538 --> 00:08:07.459
the difference in power is
as far apart as heaven and earth!

00:08:08.752 --> 00:08:09.752
I see…

00:08:09.836 --> 00:08:12.547
I don't know about your history,

00:08:12.630 --> 00:08:15.966
but in short,
it's different from Ishida's power.

00:08:16.968 --> 00:08:18.260
I'm glad to hear that.

00:08:18.552 --> 00:08:21.556
If Ishida transformed into
something as creepy as that…

00:08:21.597 --> 00:08:23.850
I might cut him down by mistake.

00:08:24.808 --> 00:08:26.769
You're easing up on your blade.

00:08:28.562 --> 00:08:31.857
Getsugatensho!

00:08:36.278 --> 00:08:38.114
That's not good.

00:08:41.033 --> 00:08:43.620
You should aim your strikes.

00:08:43.953 --> 00:08:44.955
Damn it!

00:08:46.081 --> 00:08:50.210
That said, even if you did that,
you wouldn't find any weaknesses!

00:08:51.544 --> 00:08:55.966
You called this form of mine
creepy, didn't you?

00:08:56.549 --> 00:08:58.051
That is the correct response.

00:08:58.677 --> 00:09:02.304
To the eyes of you
atrocious Soul Reapers,

00:09:02.389 --> 00:09:05.558
the form of we holy executioners…

00:09:05.808 --> 00:09:09.019
should be creepy and horrifying
to behold!

00:09:16.820 --> 00:09:19.614
No way!
Sotenkishun is being peeled away!

00:09:21.658 --> 00:09:24.326
Now have a taste…

00:09:25.077 --> 00:09:29.249
of my Voll Stern Dich,
the power of Piskiel!

00:09:33.003 --> 00:09:34.004
What…?!

00:09:40.844 --> 00:09:43.846
What is that monster?

00:09:45.599 --> 00:09:46.850
You assumed
we couldn't fight anymore,

00:09:46.932 --> 00:09:48.018
so you let down your guard,
didn't you?

00:09:48.475 --> 00:09:50.769
I thought we told you that
you shouldn't underestimate us…

00:09:51.437 --> 00:09:56.067
Show this cocky four-eyed monkey
your power!

00:09:56.567 --> 00:09:57.568
Ayon!

00:10:03.490 --> 00:10:04.491
What the hell…

00:10:04.993 --> 00:10:05.994
is that thing?!

00:10:06.870 --> 00:10:10.956
Ayon is a monster created through
the fusion of our left arms!

00:10:11.374 --> 00:10:13.626
He's got power,
but he's unpredictable!

00:10:17.004 --> 00:10:21.301
A monster like you could never
beat my Voll Stern Dich--!

00:10:24.971 --> 00:10:26.639
{\an8}ISHIDA RESIDENCE - ARCHIVES

00:10:27.557 --> 00:10:29.350
There's nothing of importance here…

00:10:29.643 --> 00:10:30.559
What are you doing?

00:10:32.979 --> 00:10:33.980
Ryuken!

00:10:34.648 --> 00:10:36.607
I thought I told you
not to come in here

00:10:36.607 --> 00:10:37.692
without my permission.

00:10:38.567 --> 00:10:42.529
The Soul Society and Hueco Mundo
are being invaded by someone.

00:10:43.657 --> 00:10:46.576
And they are most likely…Quincies.

00:10:47.701 --> 00:10:50.245
There shouldn't be any Quincies
in existence aside from us.

00:10:50.746 --> 00:10:52.164
Do you know something about this?!

00:10:54.083 --> 00:10:56.086
This has nothing to do with you.

00:10:57.836 --> 00:11:00.715
- Get out.
- Are you going to avoid me again?!

00:11:02.759 --> 00:11:04.469
I am the last Quincy.

00:11:05.302 --> 00:11:08.222
I have a right to know
what's going on.

00:11:12.309 --> 00:11:14.520
The answer you seek…

00:11:14.895 --> 00:11:15.855
cannot be found here.

00:11:18.732 --> 00:11:23.738
{\an8}SHORYU GATE ENTRANCE

00:11:24.989 --> 00:11:28.701
Shino, I know this probably isn't
the best time to ask this, but…

00:11:28.826 --> 00:11:29.744
What is it?

00:11:30.035 --> 00:11:31.955
Do you happen to know why
Soul Reapers and Quincies

00:11:32.038 --> 00:11:33.914
are at odds with each other
in the first place?

00:11:34.581 --> 00:11:37.876
We both share the same goal
of defeating Hollows, don't we?

00:11:37.961 --> 00:11:40.004
What?!
That's because…

00:11:42.090 --> 00:11:43.966
Wait…
Why is that?

00:11:44.884 --> 00:11:45.969
You know that in ancient times,

00:11:46.052 --> 00:11:48.888
Soul Reapers were referred to
as Balancers, don't you?

00:11:49.431 --> 00:11:50.056
S…

00:11:50.056 --> 00:11:52.558
{\an8}SQUAD 13 SIXTH SEAT -
HIDETOMO KAJOMARU

00:11:50.557 --> 00:11:51.765
Sixth Seat Kajomaru!

00:11:52.725 --> 00:11:53.809
It's an honor to see you here!

00:11:54.018 --> 00:11:56.229
Well, the alarms
haven't sounded yet,

00:11:56.645 --> 00:11:58.398
so why don't we discuss this a bit?

00:12:01.109 --> 00:12:02.610
For starters,

00:12:03.403 --> 00:12:05.822
you understand the law of
this world where souls circulate

00:12:05.904 --> 00:12:08.490
between the World of the Living
and the Soul Society, don't you?

00:12:08.741 --> 00:12:10.076
- Yes.
- Of course!

00:12:10.618 --> 00:12:11.619
Good.

00:12:12.162 --> 00:12:14.748
However, souls that become Hollows
in the World of the Living

00:12:15.248 --> 00:12:17.542
cannot return to the Soul Society.

00:12:18.585 --> 00:12:22.839
By purifying Hollows and delivering
their souls to the Soul Society,

00:12:23.214 --> 00:12:25.633
they are led back to
the normal circulation of souls.

00:12:26.259 --> 00:12:28.010
This is the job of Soul Reapers

00:12:28.094 --> 00:12:29.763
and the reason why
we are called Balancers.

00:12:30.679 --> 00:12:34.225
However, Quincies destroy
and completely extinguish

00:12:34.267 --> 00:12:35.769
souls that have become Hollows.

00:12:36.644 --> 00:12:37.895
What happens when they do that?

00:12:38.937 --> 00:12:42.274
The souls are unable to return
to the Soul Society?

00:12:42.775 --> 00:12:43.777
That's right.

00:12:44.110 --> 00:12:45.110
Normally,

00:12:45.153 --> 00:12:47.947
a balance must be maintained
between the number of souls

00:12:48.030 --> 00:12:50.616
that exist in the Soul Society
and the World of the Living.

00:12:51.366 --> 00:12:54.077
As Quincies extinguish more Hollows
in the World of the Living,

00:12:54.162 --> 00:12:57.539
the number of souls is diminished,
disrupting that natural balance…

00:12:58.332 --> 00:12:59.542
If we allow this to happen,

00:12:59.625 --> 00:13:01.711
the balance of souls
will eventually be ruined,

00:13:02.336 --> 00:13:04.755
causing the Soul Society to flow
into the World of the Living…

00:13:06.716 --> 00:13:08.884
ending in the simultaneous
destruction of both worlds.

00:13:13.807 --> 00:13:17.601
There isn't much written
about Quincies to begin with…

00:13:20.647 --> 00:13:21.648
Master…

00:13:27.695 --> 00:13:28.947
"Cannot be found <i>here</i>…"

00:13:30.155 --> 00:13:33.368
{\an8}ISHIDA RESIDENCE -
RYUKEN ISHIDA'S ROOM

00:13:51.260 --> 00:13:52.636
This is Master's--!

00:13:55.222 --> 00:13:56.682
To prevent this destruction,

00:13:57.015 --> 00:14:00.186
the Soul Society had repeatedly
approached the Quincies

00:14:00.269 --> 00:14:01.395
for a dialogue,

00:14:01.770 --> 00:14:03.690
but they were turned away
each time.

00:14:04.691 --> 00:14:07.235
The world was steadily
heading toward destruction.

00:14:07.902 --> 00:14:11.865
And after endless debate
within the Soul Society…

00:14:12.532 --> 00:14:14.576
the Quincy Extermination Operation

00:14:14.576 --> 00:14:17.035
was finally carried out
200 years ago.

00:14:18.037 --> 00:14:19.746
Our goals do not mesh

00:14:19.831 --> 00:14:22.958
and the grudge borne of
their genocide will never perish.

00:14:24.085 --> 00:14:28.047
The Soul Reapers and Quincies
have no other choice but to fight…

00:14:30.048 --> 00:14:32.427
Do you understand,
Squad Member Ryunosuke Yuki?

00:14:33.927 --> 00:14:36.264
May I…ask one question?

00:14:37.764 --> 00:14:41.852
Are we Soul Reapers
fighting this battle for justice?

00:14:44.730 --> 00:14:46.857
If there is justice
on one side or the other,

00:14:47.524 --> 00:14:49.735
it would be called self-defense
or conquest.

00:14:50.945 --> 00:14:52.279
However, this is a war.

00:14:53.322 --> 00:14:54.490
Wars take place…

00:14:55.283 --> 00:14:57.284
because both sides are just.

00:14:59.620 --> 00:15:02.706
You know why I've called you here,
don't you,

00:15:02.956 --> 00:15:07.961
{\an8}SQUAD 1 BARRACKS -
HEAD CAPTAIN'S OFFICE

00:15:03.291 --> 00:15:05.668
Squad 12 Captain Kurotsuchi?

00:15:06.210 --> 00:15:08.462
Is this about mobilizing
members of Squad 12

00:15:08.504 --> 00:15:12.049
to expunge 28,000 citizens
of the Rukon District

00:15:12.133 --> 00:15:15.470
without permission in order to
correct the balance of souls?

00:15:15.928 --> 00:15:18.181
Why didn't you get permission?

00:15:18.764 --> 00:15:22.059
Those mass disappearances
in the Rukon District

00:15:22.143 --> 00:15:26.105
reported by Squad 11's
Third Seat Ikkaku Madarame

00:15:26.188 --> 00:15:28.607
and Fifth Seat Yumichika Ayasegawa…

00:15:29.317 --> 00:15:32.235
You would have gotten permission
if things became dire.

00:15:32.778 --> 00:15:34.989
The mass extermination of Hollows
in the World of the Living

00:15:35.155 --> 00:15:38.158
by the rebel army was intentionally
done to disrupt the balance

00:15:38.283 --> 00:15:41.162
between the World of the Living
and the Soul Society.

00:15:41.663 --> 00:15:44.206
If you consider the fact that
the lives of the people

00:15:44.289 --> 00:15:46.583
of the Rukon District stopped
the collapse of both worlds,

00:15:46.668 --> 00:15:48.669
it is not that big of a loss.

00:15:49.044 --> 00:15:50.046
If I had waited for permission

00:15:50.129 --> 00:15:52.381
and the situation had escalated
beyond control,

00:15:52.465 --> 00:15:55.467
that is not something
I could take responsibility for.

00:15:55.884 --> 00:15:59.304
But if your Department of
Research and Development

00:15:59.471 --> 00:16:01.807
had reported the matter
and promptly dealt with it,

00:16:01.932 --> 00:16:05.061
we might have prevented
the current situation.

00:16:05.269 --> 00:16:06.645
You're wrong about that.

00:16:07.355 --> 00:16:10.149
The moment that the Quincy
known as Uryu Ishida

00:16:10.274 --> 00:16:12.985
infiltrated the Soul Society
as a Ryoka,

00:16:13.068 --> 00:16:16.489
I had already foreseen this would
happen and had given my advice.

00:16:17.240 --> 00:16:20.743
<i>You</i> are the one who chose
to needlessly disregard my words.

00:16:21.702 --> 00:16:24.496
Everything that is happening now
stems from the fact that

00:16:24.831 --> 00:16:26.707
<i>you</i>, Head Captain,

00:16:26.791 --> 00:16:32.212
couldn't kill that man
1,000 years ago!

00:16:52.607 --> 00:16:54.359
Oh, dear.

00:16:54.736 --> 00:16:57.195
But man, this guy's tough.

00:16:57.739 --> 00:16:59.699
I can't believe
he's still in one piece

00:16:59.740 --> 00:17:01.742
after that beating
he took from Ayon--

00:17:06.204 --> 00:17:07.539
Impressive…

00:17:07.749 --> 00:17:10.835
The report did not indicate
this kind of power…

00:17:11.711 --> 00:17:16.548
I must advise His Majesty
to adjust the strength of our Blut.

00:17:17.383 --> 00:17:19.301
But before I do that…

00:17:19.926 --> 00:17:22.555
Each and every one of you…

00:17:22.805 --> 00:17:25.182
will die here immediately.

00:17:28.227 --> 00:17:29.186
Not again?!

00:17:42.075 --> 00:17:43.076
Actually…

00:17:43.159 --> 00:17:44.076
Wait, Ayon!

00:17:44.367 --> 00:17:45.243
Stop!

00:17:45.536 --> 00:17:48.705
Perhaps I should say,
"you will <i>live</i> here."

00:17:57.632 --> 00:17:59.342
Sklave Rai.

00:17:59.884 --> 00:18:03.512
A Quincy's basic ability
to focus Reishi.

00:18:03.596 --> 00:18:05.263
When taken to its highest limits,

00:18:05.388 --> 00:18:07.599
it becomes the absolute
subordination of Reishi.

00:18:08.267 --> 00:18:11.144
If possible,
I didn't want to use it…

00:18:11.770 --> 00:18:17.109
because my holy wings would be
tarnished by such wicked beings.

00:18:19.528 --> 00:18:21.239
A wise decision.

00:18:21.655 --> 00:18:22.656
However,

00:18:23.281 --> 00:18:25.535
you've neglected to take
the difference in our power

00:18:25.535 --> 00:18:26.952
into consideration.

00:18:36.921 --> 00:18:38.005
Inoue!

00:18:41.550 --> 00:18:42.551
Sado!

00:18:44.261 --> 00:18:49.976
Whenever I see such a struggle,
it reaffirms my beliefs.

00:18:50.601 --> 00:18:55.522
Is the sight of the weak dying
always so unsightly?

00:18:56.022 --> 00:18:57.525
I cannot stand to watch this.

00:18:58.192 --> 00:18:59.777
Die.

00:19:10.203 --> 00:19:10.997
A Bankai…!

00:19:11.329 --> 00:19:13.249
If I destroy the disk on your head…

00:19:13.374 --> 00:19:15.250
you can't use that absolute
subordination of Reishi anymore,

00:19:15.375 --> 00:19:16.376
can you?!

00:19:16.669 --> 00:19:18.712
Figuring that out is one thing.

00:19:18.796 --> 00:19:21.339
But to actually go for it
takes courage…!

00:19:21.507 --> 00:19:23.217
You really are…

00:19:23.259 --> 00:19:25.469
difficult to deal with,
aren't you?!

00:19:28.306 --> 00:19:29.682
Hurry!
Hurry it up!

00:19:30.016 --> 00:19:31.933
Oh, come on,
what are you talking about?!

00:19:32.309 --> 00:19:35.855
You're the one who said,
<i>"We should save Dondochakka"</i>

00:19:35.980 --> 00:19:39.025
<i>"while Ichigo Kurosaki is</i>
<i>distracting the enemy!"</i>

00:19:39.066 --> 00:19:41.359
That was a close one!

00:19:41.527 --> 00:19:44.614
I didn't think we would have to
go through this much trouble!

00:19:45.198 --> 00:19:49.035
Not only are you heavy
but you chose to hide in the sand!

00:19:49.117 --> 00:19:50.536
That hurts!

00:20:00.046 --> 00:20:02.088
Don't enter without my permission.

00:20:02.548 --> 00:20:03.548
This is the second time.

00:20:03.840 --> 00:20:04.842
What's the meaning of this?

00:20:05.384 --> 00:20:07.303
Are the things written here true?

00:20:08.887 --> 00:20:11.557
I guess that means
you know everything…

00:20:12.057 --> 00:20:13.558
About the Wandenreich…

00:20:13.893 --> 00:20:15.685
About the guy
referred to as "His Majesty"…

00:20:16.394 --> 00:20:17.605
And even about Mom…!

00:20:18.564 --> 00:20:21.733
Uryu…
This has nothing to do with you.

00:20:33.246 --> 00:20:34.829
There's no need to be so tense.

00:20:35.498 --> 00:20:36.790
Sixth Seat Kajomaru…

00:20:37.666 --> 00:20:40.711
Squad 11 is standing by
outside the gate.

00:20:41.461 --> 00:20:42.672
There's no need to worry.

00:20:44.923 --> 00:20:46.592
- What was that?!
- There's a blue light!

00:20:47.175 --> 00:20:48.051
What's going on?!

00:20:49.761 --> 00:20:53.891
Conflict is such
an unpleasant affair.

00:20:56.102 --> 00:20:57.603
{\an8}SQUAD SIX BARRACKS

00:20:56.269 --> 00:20:57.603
- What's that?!
-Is it an enemy attack?!

00:20:57.686 --> 00:20:58.436
{\an8}SQUAD EIGHT BARRACKS - ENGAWA

00:20:58.520 --> 00:20:59.188
{\an8}SQUAD NINE BARRACKS -
EDITORIAL DEPARTMENT

00:20:59.271 --> 00:21:00.272
{\an8}SQUAD THREE'S GUARD AREA

00:21:00.397 --> 00:21:03.108
{\an8}SQUAD SIX'S GUARD AREA

00:21:00.690 --> 00:21:02.983
What the hell…is this?

00:21:03.150 --> 00:21:04.734
{\an8}SQUAD THIRTEEN'S GUARD AREA

00:21:05.111 --> 00:21:07.946
Flaming pillars…of Reishi?

00:21:10.324 --> 00:21:12.285
{\an8}SQUAD 1 THIRD SEAT -
GENSHIRO OKIKIBA

00:21:18.332 --> 00:21:19.625
{\an8}SQUAD 3 THIRD SEAT - RIKU TOGAKUSHI

00:21:19.709 --> 00:21:21.251
{\an8}SQUAD 3 FIFTH SEAT - TAKETSUNA GORI

00:21:21.335 --> 00:21:22.627
{\an8}SQUAD 3 SIXTH SEAT - ASUKA KATAKURA

00:21:23.045 --> 00:21:24.713
Reishi Investigation Team!
How much longer?!

00:21:25.588 --> 00:21:26.632
Spiritual Pressure detected!

00:21:26.798 --> 00:21:28.217
A 93 percent match!

00:21:28.718 --> 00:21:29.844
It's a Quincy!

00:21:39.854 --> 00:21:41.230
Lieutenant Kira!

00:21:42.480 --> 00:21:43.816
How dare you launch
a surprise attack!

00:21:44.525 --> 00:21:46.527
Spiral and Rise, Shunjin!

00:21:46.527 --> 00:21:48.695
Blow, Mogaribue!

00:21:49.739 --> 00:21:50.948
Counteract, Katakage!

00:21:58.748 --> 00:21:59.789
Sorry…

00:22:00.915 --> 00:22:03.085
but our orders are to kill you all.

00:22:11.384 --> 00:22:13.011
Tremble in fear, Soul Reapers.

00:22:14.721 --> 00:22:17.474
The Stern Ritters are going to…

00:22:19.559 --> 00:22:21.686
purge all of you.

00:22:30.488 --> 00:22:33.490
{\an8}<i>Everything we had left behind</i>

00:22:33.615 --> 00:22:37.744
{\an8}<i>Our breaths blending as mist</i>

00:22:37.827 --> 00:22:42.333
{\an8}<i>without form or expression</i>

00:22:42.458 --> 00:22:46.628
{\an8}<i>We lie buried as we glare</i>
<i>into the distance</i>

00:22:46.961 --> 00:22:49.589
{\an8}<i>I can't hear anything</i>

00:22:49.757 --> 00:22:52.634
{\an8}<i>I can't seem to cut anything</i>

00:22:52.675 --> 00:22:55.346
{\an8}<i>It feels like I'm sinking</i>

00:22:55.471 --> 00:22:57.306
{\an8}<i>Falling, falling</i>

00:22:57.390 --> 00:22:58.391
{\an8}<i>Touching</i>

00:22:58.516 --> 00:23:01.852
{\an8}<i>Eyes struck wide open</i>

00:23:01.977 --> 00:23:05.230
{\an8}<i>Something no one has ever seen</i>

00:23:05.355 --> 00:23:11.528
{\an8}<i>The furthest reaches are now visible to us</i>

00:23:11.612 --> 00:23:15.490
{\an8}<i>It cannot be undone</i>
<i>and cannot be stopped</i>

00:23:15.615 --> 00:23:18.827
{\an8}<i>This ensuing struggle</i>

00:23:19.077 --> 00:23:23.624
{\an8}<i>Whisk it away beyond</i>
<i>the ends of the earth</i>

00:23:23.624 --> 00:23:25.667
{\an8}<i>Along with our breaths</i>

00:23:26.126 --> 00:23:27.420
{\an8}<i>Take everything</i>

00:23:27.502 --> 00:23:32.173
{\an8}<i>Whisk it away beyond</i>
<i>the ends of the earth</i>

00:23:32.298 --> 00:23:34.218
{\an8}<i>Along with our futures</i>

00:23:34.343 --> 00:23:36.095
{\an8}<i>Along with our world</i>

00:23:37.179 --> 00:23:40.516
{\an8}<i>Something no one has ever seen</i>

00:23:40.598 --> 00:23:46.814
{\an8}<i>The furthest reaches are now</i>
<i>visible to us</i>

00:23:46.939 --> 00:23:48.941
{\an8}<i>Don't you know God's demand?</i>

00:23:49.107 --> 00:23:50.608
{\an8}<i>Don't you know God's demand?</i>

00:23:50.776 --> 00:23:54.363
{\an8}<i>As we tear each other down</i>

00:23:58.909 --> 00:24:03.455
<i>"A frostbitten world turns to fire,</i>
<i>a shadow of a wing remains."</i>

00:24:04.664 --> 00:24:10.546
<i>"I try and try again,</i>
<i>it slips away, shadow of a wing."</i>

